<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,1861,1993]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
“Black somewhat shining; vertex of head with the anterior margin ochraceous; face dull ochraceous, lateral areas with dark striations, cheeks black; femora black, their apices and the tibiae and tarsi dark ochraceous; vertex of head (excluding anterior margin) thickly finely punctate and with a central longitudinal carination; pronotum and scutellum closely transversely striate; tegmina thickly, coarsely punctate” (
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[988,1145,1969,1993]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" refId="ref72103" refString="Distant, W. L. (1918) Rhynchota. Homoptera, Appendix, Heteroptera, Addenda. In: Shipley, A. E. &amp; Marshall, G. A. K (eds) The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Volume VII, viii + 210 pp. Taylor &amp; Francis, London." type="book" year="1918">Distant, 1918</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
