<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,151,496]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Head rounded but longer medially than next to eyes. Genae strongly concave beneath eyes. Lora narrow and long, reaching nearly half length between base of antennae and transclypeal sulcus. Elongate spot at base of antennae black. Clypellus extending beyond normal curve of gena, apically bilobed.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,151,496]" box="[199,1157,258,283]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,258,283]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="1">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Hind margin of seventh sternite with V-shaped median excavation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,151,496]" box="[199,922,294,318]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,294,318]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="1">Measurements.</emphasis>
